President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of New Hampshire and has ordered Federal assistance to supplement State and local recovery efforts following a severe winter storm and snowstorm that occurred from March 13 to March 14, 2018. The Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, snow removal, and hazard mitigation measures. James N. Russo has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made based on the results of damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.